          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500"> ICC warrants on Taliban leaders </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>Summary: The ICC issued arrest warrants for Taliban leaders over alleged crimes against women.</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> The International Criminal Court (ICC) <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-issued-arrest-warrants" target="_blank">issued arrest warrants</a> for Afghanistan‚Äôs Taliban leader Haibatullah Akhundzada and chief justice Abdul Hakim Haqqani. They are accused of crimes against humanity for their treatment of women and girls since 2021. Charges include <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-bans-on-education" target="_blank">bans on education</a> for girls over 12, restrictions on work, travel, speech, and repression of gender rights.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The response:</strong> The Taliban dismissed the ICC‚Äôs authority and called the warrant a measure of hostility. They claim that the government respects women's rights according to its interpretation of Afghan culture and <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-spotlight-h2-7-islamic-law" target="_blank">Islamic law</a>.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The pressure:</strong> The UN General Assembly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-spotlight-h2-8-adopted-a-resolution" target="_blank">adopted a resolution</a> calling on the Taliban rulers to end their oppression of women and girls. While the resolution is not legally binding, it is seen as a reflection of the world‚Äôs opposition to the Taliban policies.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
