              padding-bottom: 6px;
            ">
            <strong>üá®üá¶ Canada - Militia foiled.</strong> Four men in Quebec, including two active personnel of the Canadian Armed Forces, were arrested for allegedly planning to create an anti-government militia and seize land near Quebec City. The men participated in military-style training and firearms exercises, and the Canadian police say it is a case of ideologically motivated violent extremism (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-worldwide-12-the-story" target="_blank">the story</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong>üáπüá≥ Tunisia - Opposition arrested.</strong> Tunisian opposition leader Rached Ghannouchi, head of the Ennahda party, was sentenced to 14 years in prison for conspiring against state security. This is part of a series of sentences against him and other opposition figures, amid an ongoing crackdown on dissent under President Kais Saied (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-worldwide-13-tunisia-s-political-crisis" target="_blank">Tunisia‚Äôs political crisis</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong>üá´üá∑ France - Police raid far-right headquarters.</strong> Marine Le Pen‚Äôs party faces scrutiny over alleged illegal campaign financing. Police raided their headquarters and seized documents tied to recent elections. Investigators suspect that illegal liabilities and fake invoices are being used. Le Pen, recently banned from office after being convicted of falsifying job applications, has tapped Jordan Bardella to run in her place in 2027. Le Pen denies wrongdoing (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-worldwide-14-le-pen-in-hot-water" target="_blank">Le Pen in hot water</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong>üáßüá© Bangladesh - Leaked conversation.</strong> Sheikh Hasina, Bangladesh's former PM, is accused of authorizing lethal force during student-led protests in 2024, which killed up to 1,400 people. A leaked audio conversation, verified by experts, captures her ordering security forces to shoot protesters. Tried in absentia for crimes against humanity, Hasina denies any wrongdoing (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-worldwide-15-about-the-conversation" target="_blank">about the conversation</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
            <strong>üá∞üá∑ South Korea - Ex-president arrested again.</strong> Former South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol has been rearrested based on five key charges, including violation of the rights of cabinet persons and concerns over evidence tampering. If convicted, Yoon could face imprisonment or the death penalty (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-10-jul-25-worldwide-16-back-behind-bars" target="_blank">back behind bars</a>).
          </p>
